<br>
So you find Kiddie games boring? Honestly, have you been to a game store lately? There are way to many &quot;T&quot; and &quot;M&quot; rated titles (for GameCube ) to count. <br>
   The last game I played on Game Cube I've killed more people in one day than I have withen a week of playing GTA 3. And who had to censor BMX XXX? Not Nintendo.<br>
    Seriously though, I'm glad there are good E rated games like Zelda and Mario. In fact, if you find a game boring because there is no blood I'd recommend not buying any console, period. I'd also recommend help. <br>
<br>
To me, a mature gamer doesn't care about the rating - only the game itself. Like said before, if you want gameplay over violence, grab a Cube or Box. <br>
<br>
PS2 may have more exclusive titles, but that isn't always a good thing. A lot of games are now multi-system, usually with X box having the better graphics, then GC, then PS2. <br>
Most times when a game goes from X-Box to GC, it loses some visual effects but makes up for it with more balanced gameplay and some cool GBA feature which can affect the whole game itself. PS2 also loses visual effects but gains the balanced gameplay and maybe adds a new level. <br>
<br>
However, if you like RPG's, go with a PS2.  <p>--The only things I want to give you are orders. </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=agentcryrid>Agent Cryrid</A> at: 4/19/03 8:04:56 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=slashartist@polykarbonbbs>Slash Artist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/19/03 5:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  ok...</span><hr size=1>  Wow Cyrid calm down...I just meant that I dont find Spiderman and Super Mario Sunshine exactly enthraling... I play alot of games that don't have gore in them I just think that Gamecube is releasing alot more child-geared games(as Nintendo always has) than the other two are going to. All the good RPG's are going to PS2 so I'll stay with my choice thanks... o by the way...<br>
