<br>
True, Nintendo games are good all-ages fare. Nobody argues that, but sometimes you just don't want to play those.<br>
If you've got a hankerin' to play fighters or RPGs, the Gamecube lacks. XBox less so, but it does too. I have no interest in more Mario Sunshine either, since I never really got into the game the first time (when it was called Mario 64 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). I did play through Zelda. Occasionally I'm playing Metroid...but that's a Teen game. Yeah, they're fun. <br>
<br>
Sometimes though, I want to have a better story or a more realistic environment. It's there that a lot of games are pushing new boundries. Mario and Zelda are good, fun games. They've also been good, fun games for 15 years or so at this point. There's nothing superior or enlightened about realizing that they're good, and the formula has been polished for so long that they <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>better be</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. <br>
<br>
Games like Splinter Cell, GTAIII, Deus Ex, Half Life, Neverwinter Nights, Warcraft, etc etc etc are not for all ages. But they're still good games, and some have pushed storytelling in games a bit beyond what it could have been in games designed for everyone. Have I played a game where Ganon captures Princess Zelda or Mario has to fight Bowser? Heck yeah, and I had a good time. Have I played a game where I can choose to play it without killing any non major characters or choose to kill them all? Not before I played Deus Ex (not to mention all the other stuff that game has going for it). Nintendo has innovative games occasionally...and you'll then see versions of that game for then next couple decades <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Many of the newer, fresher games have been Teen or Mature though. I can understand why someone would want to jump to those. I agree, one would miss out by totally dropping all ages games...but that doesn't mean that's all that's good either. Blood and violence in games are often simply the result of more realistic stories or settings. If that's what someone is interested in, then cool.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=648.topic&start=21&stop=37>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=648.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=648.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.emailToFriend?topicID=648.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.threadControl?topicID=648.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=648.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=648.topic>